WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.421 --> 00:00:05.631
[ Groans ]

2
00:00:06.507 --> 00:00:08.050
Ah. ugh.

3
00:00:08.133 --> 00:00:09.968
Oh. God.
Oh. God.

4
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:12.012
[ Urinating ]

5
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:12.012
Mmm!

6
00:00:13.931 --> 00:00:15.098
[ Glass shatters ]

7
00:00:15.140 --> 00:00:17.476
Oh. Oh. God.

8
00:00:17.559 --> 00:00:19.061
[ Coughs ]

9
00:00:19.144 --> 00:00:20.062
[ Burps loudly ]

10
00:00:20.145 --> 00:00:23.398
[ Drunkenly muttering ]

11
00:00:24.149 --> 00:00:25.400
[ Grunts ]

12
00:00:26.026 --> 00:00:27.778
Oh. ugh.

13
00:00:29.238 --> 00:00:31.323
Mmm. mmm. mmm.

14
00:00:31.365 --> 00:00:32.658
[ Glass shatters ]

15
00:00:32.741 --> 00:00:34.159
Ugh. this fuckin' thing.

16
00:00:34.243 --> 00:00:36.537
This. uh. uhh. fuck.

17
00:00:36.620 --> 00:00:37.496
Ho...kay.

18
00:00:37.579 --> 00:00:38.914
[ Error dings ]

19
00:00:37.579 --> 00:00:38.914
Come o-o-on!

20
00:00:38.997 --> 00:00:40.249
Come on. man!

21
00:00:38.997 --> 00:00:40.249
[ Error dings ]

22
00:00:40.290 --> 00:00:42.834
Piece of fuckin' --
piece of shit!

23
00:00:42.876 --> 00:00:45.337
[ Error dings ]

24
00:00:42.876 --> 00:00:45.337
Aah! Aah!

25
00:00:46.922 --> 00:00:50.175
Hnn. hnn. hnn. hnn. <i>hnn!</i>

26
00:00:50.259 --> 00:00:52.344
[ Error dings ]

27
00:00:50.259 --> 00:00:52.344
<i>Lockdown initiated.</i>

28
00:00:52.386 --> 00:00:54.763
[ Machinery whirring ]

29
00:00:57.641 --> 00:00:59.810
Mort-y-y-y!

30
00:01:01.228 --> 00:01:03.689
Ohhh. Hey. pal.
W-what's up?

31
00:01:03.730 --> 00:01:06.358
Oh. g-good --
good morning. Mor-- Morty.

32
00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:07.818
Yeah. Sure thing.

33
00:01:07.859 --> 00:01:09.736
You want breakfast?

34
00:01:09.820 --> 00:01:11.238
Or dinner?

35
00:01:11.321 --> 00:01:13.865
Are you <i>humoring</i> me.
Morty?

36
00:01:13.907 --> 00:01:15.200
[ Sighs ]
No.

37
00:01:15.242 --> 00:01:17.119
I only had a couple
of drinks. Morty!

38
00:01:17.202 --> 00:01:19.204
S-so. w-what do you
need me for?

39
00:01:19.246 --> 00:01:22.916
This fuckin' thing
locked me out!

40
00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:24.710
Okay. Well.
whose fault is that?

41
00:01:24.793 --> 00:01:26.128
Y-o-o-ours!

42
00:01:24.793 --> 00:01:26.128
What?

43
00:01:26.211 --> 00:01:27.879
Let! Me! In!

44
00:01:27.963 --> 00:01:28.964
[ Electricity crackles ]

45
00:01:27.963 --> 00:01:28.964
Owww!

46
00:01:29.047 --> 00:01:29.965
Unh!

47
00:01:30.048 --> 00:01:33.427
M-o-o-o-ort-y-y-y-y!

48
00:01:33.510 --> 00:01:36.305
I mean. Rick. I don't really
know what I can do here.

49
00:01:36.388 --> 00:01:38.807
Y-you don't give a shit
about grandpa. huh?

50
00:01:38.849 --> 00:01:40.267
Is -- Is that it. Morty?
Y-you want me dead?

51
00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:41.727
[ Sighs ]
Rick...

52
00:01:41.768 --> 00:01:44.563
Y-you won't inherit
anything from me. Morty.

53
00:01:44.605 --> 00:01:46.857
Evil boy. Wicked boy.

54
00:01:44.605 --> 00:01:46.857
[ Cellphone ringing ]

55
00:01:46.898 --> 00:01:48.233
Okay.
You know what?

56
00:01:48.317 --> 00:01:50.611
Hello? R-Rick S--
Rick Sanchez phone.

57
00:01:50.694 --> 00:01:52.487
How'd -- How you
get this number?

58
00:01:53.030 --> 00:01:54.406
Reese!

59
00:01:53.030 --> 00:01:54.406
Reese?

60
00:01:54.448 --> 00:01:56.366
Uh. y-you're in town?
Of course we can.

61
00:01:56.408 --> 00:01:59.161
Of course I'm drunk.
L-let's. uh. see you soon!

62
00:01:59.202 --> 00:02:01.371
Guess who that was!

63
00:01:59.202 --> 00:02:01.371
It was Reese.

64
00:02:01.413 --> 00:02:03.081
Y-you said --
You said it out loud!

65
00:02:03.123 --> 00:02:05.000
Fucking Reese. Morty!

66
00:02:05.083 --> 00:02:07.044
Mnhmnh.
who needs passwords. huh?

67
00:02:07.085 --> 00:02:10.297
W-we need our minds
off of this <i>shit.</i> Morty.

68
00:02:10.380 --> 00:02:12.424
We gotta hang out
with our pal Reese!

69
00:02:12.466 --> 00:02:15.052
Rick. you just yelled at me.
and I don't even care.

70
00:02:15.093 --> 00:02:16.595
I like Reese that much.

71
00:02:16.678 --> 00:02:18.430
[burps] That's 'cause
he's the fuckin' best!

72
00:02:18.513 --> 00:02:20.057
You got that right.

73
00:02:20.098 --> 00:02:21.725
[ Downbeat rock music plays ]

74
00:02:21.767 --> 00:02:23.185
{\an8}♪♪

75
00:02:23.268 --> 00:02:26.521
Reese! Reese! Reese!
Reese! Reese! Reese!

76
00:02:26.605 --> 00:02:36.531
{\an8}♪♪

77
00:02:36.615 --> 00:02:46.541
{\an8}♪♪

78
00:02:46.625 --> 00:02:54.216
{\an8}♪♪

79
00:02:54.299 --> 00:02:55.926
[ Electricity crackles ]

80
00:03:01.264 --> 00:03:02.849
{\an8}I love these trips. Reese.

81
00:03:02.933 --> 00:03:04.142
{\an8}H-hell. yeah!

82
00:03:04.184 --> 00:03:05.852
{\an8}Fly-fishing. babay!

83
00:03:05.936 --> 00:03:06.853
{\an8}[ Reel whirs ]

84
00:03:06.937 --> 00:03:07.896
{\an8}[ Snap! ]

85
00:03:07.979 --> 00:03:09.439
{\an8}Aww!
W-was that my fault?

86
00:03:09.481 --> 00:03:10.732
{\an8}D-did I
fuck that up?

87
00:03:10.816 --> 00:03:13.151
{\an8}M-dawg.
if they never got away.

88
00:03:13.193 --> 00:03:14.861
{\an8}what'd be the point
of catching 'em?

89
00:03:14.945 --> 00:03:18.240
{\an8}Man. that's some great --
great fly-fishing wisdom. Reese.

90
00:03:18.323 --> 00:03:19.658
{\an8}Really calming.

91
00:03:19.700 --> 00:03:21.243
{\an8}You gotta wade
with the current. dude.

92
00:03:21.326 --> 00:03:22.703
{\an8}You're the best.

93
00:03:21.326 --> 00:03:22.703
{\an8}[ Reel whirs ]

94
00:03:22.786 --> 00:03:24.287
{\an8}Awww. geez!

95
00:03:24.329 --> 00:03:25.497
{\an8}Hey. M-Morty.

96
00:03:25.539 --> 00:03:27.332
{\an8}Morty. Morty.
Morty. Morty!

97
00:03:27.416 --> 00:03:28.542
{\an8}Oh! Oh. God!
Rick!

98
00:03:28.625 --> 00:03:30.836
{\an8}[ Chuckles ]
Get outta here!

99
00:03:30.919 --> 00:03:32.504
{\an8}[ Laughing ]

100
00:03:32.587 --> 00:03:34.297
{\an8}[ Insects chirping ]

101
00:03:34.339 --> 00:03:36.425
{\an8}I <i>know</i> I packed
the special marshmallows.

102
00:03:36.508 --> 00:03:38.552
{\an8}One job.

103
00:03:36.508 --> 00:03:38.552
{\an8}I opened the cabinet.

104
00:03:38.635 --> 00:03:40.220
{\an8}I looked at them.
I <i>know</i> I looked at them!

105
00:03:40.303 --> 00:03:41.805
{\an8}One job!

106
00:03:41.847 --> 00:03:43.432
{\an8}You forgot them
on the last Reese trip.

107
00:03:43.515 --> 00:03:45.434
{\an8}Seems like a bad thing
to trust me with. then.

108
00:03:45.517 --> 00:03:47.561
{\an8}You gotta be more patient
with Morty. Rick.

109
00:03:47.644 --> 00:03:49.438
{\an8}Not everyone
can be a genius.

110
00:03:49.479 --> 00:03:52.816
{\an8}It's what you do with
what you got that counts.

111
00:03:53.525 --> 00:03:55.652
{\an8}Sorry. Morty.
I could take it easier on you.

112
00:03:55.694 --> 00:03:58.155
{\an8}I'm. uh -- I'm still wired
from catching all those fish.

113
00:03:58.196 --> 00:04:02.159
{\an8}Ha ha! Well. you'd find a way
to get high on anything.

114
00:04:02.200 --> 00:04:03.702
{\an8}Ain't that the truth?

115
00:04:03.785 --> 00:04:05.370
{\an8}[ All laughing ]

116
00:04:05.412 --> 00:04:06.538
{\an8}Rick: True.

117
00:04:06.705 --> 00:04:08.540
{\an8}You know. Rick.
you two may fight.

118
00:04:08.582 --> 00:04:11.126
{\an8}but you're the real deal.

119
00:04:11.168 --> 00:04:13.336
{\an8}[ Watch dings ]

120
00:04:11.168 --> 00:04:13.336
{\an8}Heh. Thanks. Reese.

121
00:04:13.378 --> 00:04:14.504
{\an8}[ Cellphone vibrates ]

122
00:04:14.546 --> 00:04:16.923
{\an8}Ah. man.
I hate to do this. guys.

123
00:04:17.007 --> 00:04:19.384
{\an8}but I got some work stuff
I still need to hit.

124
00:04:19.426 --> 00:04:20.719
{\an8}Might have to call it.

125
00:04:20.802 --> 00:04:22.596
{\an8}[burps] Sounds good to me.
I'm beat.

126
00:04:22.679 --> 00:04:24.765
{\an8}What? The --
The trip just started.

127
00:04:24.848 --> 00:04:27.809
{\an8}Sorry. champ. but the river's
not going anywhere.

128
00:04:27.851 --> 00:04:31.021
{\an8}Shake a leg. Morty.
Some of us got
responsibilities.

129
00:04:32.397 --> 00:04:33.732
{\an8}[ Bottles clattering ]

130
00:04:34.441 --> 00:04:36.276
{\an8}You could always just
move to Earth. Reese.

131
00:04:36.359 --> 00:04:37.736
{\an8}Rick's a god.

132
00:04:37.778 --> 00:04:39.321
{\an8}He could. like.
grow your job out of slime.

133
00:04:39.404 --> 00:04:41.239
{\an8}He could grow your
whole company out of slime.

134
00:04:41.281 --> 00:04:43.074
{\an8}It's a great idea. Morty.

135
00:04:43.116 --> 00:04:44.785
{\an8}I'll pitch it to my boss.

136
00:04:44.868 --> 00:04:46.036
{\an8}Bye. Reese.

137
00:04:46.787 --> 00:04:49.748
{\an8}Remember. wade with
the current. pal.

138
00:04:49.790 --> 00:04:52.292
{\an8}[ Machinery whirring ]

139
00:04:49.790 --> 00:04:52.292
{\an8}Theft detected.

140
00:04:54.544 --> 00:04:56.963
{\an8}Um. did -- did --
did you just...

141
00:04:58.423 --> 00:05:00.050
{\an8}Threat nullified.

142
00:05:00.091 --> 00:05:02.385
{\an8}Shit.

143
00:05:00.091 --> 00:05:02.385
{\an8}Jesus fucking Christ!

144
00:05:02.427 --> 00:05:04.596
{\an8}Okay. so. Morty.
I know your instinct will be

145
00:05:04.638 --> 00:05:06.264
{\an8}to make a big deal
about this.

146
00:05:06.306 --> 00:05:08.016
{\an8}You'll be all.
"Betrayal! Betrayal!"

147
00:05:08.058 --> 00:05:09.768
{\an8}We've known him
for years!

148
00:05:09.810 --> 00:05:13.396
{\an8}S-so Reese takes us camping
whenever you get locked out?!

149
00:05:13.438 --> 00:05:16.233
{\an8}Oh. my God.
Am I your fucking password?

150
00:05:16.274 --> 00:05:18.193
{\an8}Ugh. It's more complex
than that.

151
00:05:18.276 --> 00:05:19.736
{\an8}But yes.

152
00:05:19.778 --> 00:05:21.571
{\an8}Our relationship is
unique in the multiverse.

153
00:05:21.613 --> 00:05:22.948
{\an8}Th-there.
Jerk off to it.

154
00:05:22.989 --> 00:05:24.699
{\an8}It's what
you <i>always</i> wanted.

155
00:05:24.783 --> 00:05:26.284
{\an8}We're unique.
and I depend on you.

156
00:05:26.368 --> 00:05:27.452
{\an8}Unh!

157
00:05:26.368 --> 00:05:27.452
{\an8}Whoa!

158
00:05:27.494 --> 00:05:29.287
{\an8}And you needed to gaslight me

159
00:05:29.329 --> 00:05:31.456
{\an8}with a cool fake friend
to verify that?!

160
00:05:31.540 --> 00:05:32.958
{\an8}Morty. how can you
be mad at this?

161
00:05:33.041 --> 00:05:35.710
{\an8}I created an awesome guy
we had a great time with.

162
00:05:35.794 --> 00:05:37.629
{\an8}I'm more sad about this
than you. Morty.

163
00:05:37.671 --> 00:05:39.464
{\an8}I liked Reese.
Reese was cool.

164
00:05:39.548 --> 00:05:42.300
{\an8}Now I gotta build
a new fuckin' Reese thing!

165
00:05:42.384 --> 00:05:43.426
{\an8}[ Grunting ]

166
00:05:43.468 --> 00:05:45.387
{\an8}Unh! Hunh!
Uhh! Unh!

167
00:05:45.470 --> 00:05:46.638
{\an8}Unh!

168
00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:47.430
{\an8}Aah!

169
00:05:47.472 --> 00:05:50.809
{\an8}[ Muffled screaming ]

170
00:05:50.851 --> 00:05:54.145
{\an8}[ Muffled screaming continues ]

171
00:05:54.187 --> 00:05:55.981
{\an8}Mm. Mm.

172
00:05:56.064 --> 00:05:59.609
{\an8}Mm. Mm. Mm. Mm.

173
00:05:59.651 --> 00:06:01.111
{\an8}[ Gulping loudly ]

174
00:06:02.404 --> 00:06:04.364
{\an8}Ahh. Oh.

175
00:06:04.447 --> 00:06:06.700
{\an8}[ Gulping continues ]

176
00:06:11.121 --> 00:06:12.998
Ahh.
[ Sighs ]

177
00:06:13.915 --> 00:06:18.211
What?

178
00:06:13.915 --> 00:06:18.211
It's just. how is there
that much liquid in there?

179
00:06:18.295 --> 00:06:21.172
Oh. Uh. this one is. uh --
it's a -- it's a portal thing.

180
00:06:21.214 --> 00:06:23.884
Th-there's a big silo full
of vodka on this one planet.

181
00:06:23.967 --> 00:06:26.636
These. uh. little hog-men
keep it full for me.

182
00:06:26.678 --> 00:06:29.931
Okay.

183
00:06:26.678 --> 00:06:29.931
I'm gonna go
[burps] empty it.

184
00:06:33.059 --> 00:06:34.477
Ugh!

185
00:06:36.897 --> 00:06:38.148
Rick?

186
00:06:38.189 --> 00:06:40.191
That was fucked up. Rick.

187
00:06:40.233 --> 00:06:41.568
But I can handle fucked up.

188
00:06:41.651 --> 00:06:43.945
A-a-and now
that I know what Reese is.

189
00:06:43.987 --> 00:06:46.823
w-we can. we can hang out
with him all the time. right?

190
00:06:46.865 --> 00:06:48.867
Uh...

191
00:06:46.865 --> 00:06:48.867
Morty wha-whaa?

192
00:06:48.950 --> 00:06:51.202
What the hell
are you doing to him?

193
00:06:51.244 --> 00:06:56.499
Oh. I got. I gotta transfer over
some stuff-uh before disposal.

194
00:06:56.541 --> 00:06:57.876
"Disposal"?!

195
00:06:57.918 --> 00:07:00.420
Reese is a liability. Morty.

196
00:06:57.918 --> 00:07:00.420
[ Device beeps ]

197
00:07:00.503 --> 00:07:01.963
He's like a credit card.

198
00:07:02.047 --> 00:07:03.590
If he's not in use.
he-e's gotta be shredded.

199
00:07:03.673 --> 00:07:05.091
Chin up. Morty.

200
00:07:05.175 --> 00:07:08.219
It's my bad for going all
Iron Giant in front of ya.

201
00:07:08.303 --> 00:07:09.471
I don't want
you to die.

202
00:07:09.554 --> 00:07:11.723
Hey. hey. hey.
I'm not dying...

203
00:07:11.765 --> 00:07:13.224
'cause I was never
really living.

204
00:07:13.308 --> 00:07:15.393
[ Slurring ] He's got all
my passwords. Morty.

205
00:07:15.435 --> 00:07:18.605
You can't just -- he's not
a guy. he's -- he's a wallet.

206
00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:19.898
Nice wallet.

207
00:07:19.940 --> 00:07:21.483
Aah! Morty!

208
00:07:21.566 --> 00:07:23.360
[ Errors dinging ]

209
00:07:23.401 --> 00:07:25.236
<i>Lockdown initiated.</i>

210
00:07:25.278 --> 00:07:26.404
[ Machinery whirring ]

211
00:07:26.488 --> 00:07:27.948
Morty. nooo!

212
00:07:29.074 --> 00:07:30.992
Aah! Ooh! Ohh!

213
00:07:31.076 --> 00:07:32.452
[ Groans ]

214
00:07:32.535 --> 00:07:34.746
[ Pounding on hatch ]

215
00:07:34.829 --> 00:07:36.414
[ Honking. horn blares ]

216
00:07:36.456 --> 00:07:38.708
[ Meow! Bonk! ]

217
00:07:36.456 --> 00:07:38.708
[ Man yodeling ]

218
00:07:38.750 --> 00:07:40.460
[ Intercom static ]

219
00:07:38.750 --> 00:07:40.460
Reese is my <i>friend!</i>

220
00:07:40.543 --> 00:07:41.962
Rick:
<i>He's not</i> alive. <i>Morty!</i>

221
00:07:42.045 --> 00:07:44.631
He's-- he's a program
that unlocks my computer

222
00:07:44.714 --> 00:07:46.049
and dispenses clichés!

223
00:07:46.091 --> 00:07:48.259
<i>You better open
that hatch. Morty!</i>

224
00:07:52.222 --> 00:07:53.598
[ Switch clicks ]

225
00:07:53.640 --> 00:07:56.059
Reese?
Ar-are you okay?

226
00:07:56.101 --> 00:07:57.185
Whoa!

227
00:07:57.268 --> 00:07:58.645
I'm a bit worried.

228
00:07:58.728 --> 00:08:00.730
I mean. what happens
when Rick reels us in?

229
00:08:00.772 --> 00:08:02.440
Guess I can drop
the folksy act.

230
00:08:02.482 --> 00:08:04.776
No. I-I like it.
It's part of the charm.

231
00:08:04.818 --> 00:08:06.486
Well. then where are
we casting off?

232
00:08:06.569 --> 00:08:08.029
There's an old
landline portal down here.

233
00:08:08.113 --> 00:08:09.656
Level 17.

234
00:08:09.739 --> 00:08:11.032
W-we'll figure it out
from there.

235
00:08:11.116 --> 00:08:12.742
Aye-aye. Captain!

236
00:08:13.284 --> 00:08:15.286
Maybe a lighter touch.

237
00:08:16.830 --> 00:08:18.748
{\an8}[ Device powering up ]

238
00:08:19.958 --> 00:08:20.959
Aah!

239
00:08:24.087 --> 00:08:26.297
Neighbor: Ohh!!
The TV froze!

240
00:08:26.381 --> 00:08:27.882
Now what do I think?!

241
00:08:32.137 --> 00:08:33.805
[ Line ringing ]

242
00:08:33.847 --> 00:08:35.849
Huge Clouds Metallurgy.

243
00:08:35.932 --> 00:08:38.143
Rick: <i>You guys
helped me build a lock.</i>

244
00:08:38.184 --> 00:08:39.811
That's right. we did.

245
00:08:39.853 --> 00:08:41.062
Rick: <i>I locked it
with the keys inside.</i>

246
00:08:41.104 --> 00:08:43.314
That is gonna take
some metallurgy.

247
00:08:43.398 --> 00:08:45.984
You said it. How soon can
your technician get here?

248
00:08:46.026 --> 00:08:48.695
<i>Hmm. We need
remote system access.</i>

249
00:08:48.778 --> 00:08:50.405
Can do. One sec.

250
00:08:50.780 --> 00:08:51.990
Hey. Jerry. call for you.

251
00:08:52.073 --> 00:08:56.327
Yello--
ooughughuhglugughh!

252
00:08:56.369 --> 00:08:57.829
Ho-ho-hoo-hoo!

253
00:08:57.912 --> 00:08:59.497
Yeah. yeah. you're
a bipedal simian now.

254
00:08:59.539 --> 00:09:03.168
in a gravity of 9.8 MPS.
Don't. don't get any ideas.

255
00:09:03.251 --> 00:09:05.712
So much m-a-a-a-ass.

256
00:09:07.589 --> 00:09:10.967
Sorry. sorry.
You said the lock was...?

257
00:09:13.762 --> 00:09:15.013
This is interesting.

258
00:09:15.096 --> 00:09:17.599
We don't sell this model
double-bonded.

259
00:09:17.682 --> 00:09:20.018
I know.
Did that a-ma-self.

260
00:09:20.060 --> 00:09:20.852
[ Whistles ]

261
00:09:20.935 --> 00:09:23.646
This is qu-a-a-ality work.

262
00:09:23.688 --> 00:09:24.856
Oh. thanks.
Heh.

263
00:09:24.939 --> 00:09:27.817
Of course.
it does void the warranty.

264
00:09:27.859 --> 00:09:31.112
What?

265
00:09:27.859 --> 00:09:31.112
I'll need access
to this whole thing.

266
00:09:31.196 --> 00:09:33.239
Might have to
dig it all out.

267
00:09:33.323 --> 00:09:36.534
Is there a place where I could
get tools and things?

268
00:09:36.618 --> 00:09:38.203
For this?

269
00:09:36.618 --> 00:09:38.203
A hardware store?

270
00:09:38.286 --> 00:09:40.538
Yes...

271
00:09:38.286 --> 00:09:40.538
And you're
not just stalling

272
00:09:40.622 --> 00:09:42.040
'cause you wanna
take this new body out

273
00:09:42.082 --> 00:09:43.875
for a sensory
flight of fancy?

274
00:09:43.958 --> 00:09:45.835
Noooo...

275
00:09:46.711 --> 00:09:49.255
Remember.
whole subbasement!

276
00:09:49.339 --> 00:09:51.382
Dug out!
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

277
00:09:52.675 --> 00:09:54.594
Should be
a straight shot to 17.

278
00:09:54.677 --> 00:09:56.054
Just have to...

279
00:09:56.137 --> 00:09:57.847
c-cut. cut through
the prison level...

280
00:09:57.889 --> 00:10:00.225
[ Ominous music plays ]

281
00:10:00.308 --> 00:10:02.811
Hey. those weapons
you used earlier to. uh.

282
00:10:02.852 --> 00:10:04.562
kill that raccoon --

283
00:10:02.852 --> 00:10:04.562
Destroy the intruder.

284
00:10:04.646 --> 00:10:06.397
Destroy the intruder!
That's better.

285
00:10:06.439 --> 00:10:08.566
Uh. can you use those...
whenever?

286
00:10:08.608 --> 00:10:09.901
Not really.

287
00:10:09.984 --> 00:10:11.277
I mean. just on things
that threaten you.

288
00:10:11.361 --> 00:10:12.821
the house. or Rick.

289
00:10:12.862 --> 00:10:17.117
So you can destroy things
that are hurting me.

290
00:10:18.493 --> 00:10:19.494
Yes.

291
00:10:19.577 --> 00:10:21.746
Aw. geez.

292
00:10:21.788 --> 00:10:23.039
[ Inhales deeply ]

293
00:10:23.081 --> 00:10:25.583
Unh! Unh!
Unh! Unh!

294
00:10:25.667 --> 00:10:26.918
[ Whirring ]

295
00:10:28.336 --> 00:10:30.672
Threat nullified.

296
00:10:30.755 --> 00:10:32.340
[ Groans ]
Here we go.

297
00:10:32.382 --> 00:10:35.093
There should be no shortage
of threats in here.

298
00:10:36.594 --> 00:10:38.429
Thank fucking God.

299
00:10:38.513 --> 00:10:39.889
That was gonna suck.

300
00:10:39.931 --> 00:10:41.975
Aw. I was fixing
to have me a hootenanny

301
00:10:42.058 --> 00:10:43.226
like you wouldn't believe.

302
00:10:43.268 --> 00:10:44.769
Revenge!!

303
00:10:43.268 --> 00:10:44.769
Aah!

304
00:10:47.438 --> 00:10:49.566
He grabbed your leg
and screamed "revenge."

305
00:10:49.607 --> 00:10:51.109
No. no.
a-all that buildup.

306
00:10:51.151 --> 00:10:53.194
I'm glad
<i>something</i> happened.

307
00:10:53.903 --> 00:10:56.948
Morty I -- I don't actually know
what "hootenanny" means.

308
00:10:57.031 --> 00:10:58.908
It's okay.
We're almost there.

309
00:10:58.950 --> 00:11:00.285
[ Drill whirring ]

310
00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:03.705
Where the fuck
is that guy?

311
00:11:03.788 --> 00:11:05.290
Beth: D-a-a-ad?

312
00:11:05.331 --> 00:11:07.625
Where's Jerry?!

313
00:11:07.667 --> 00:11:10.211
Rick: That's exactly
what I'm wondering!

314
00:11:11.004 --> 00:11:12.547
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

315
00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:15.300
[ Humming ]

316
00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:15.300
Hello?

317
00:11:15.341 --> 00:11:17.677
That doesn't sound
like a hardware store.

318
00:11:17.760 --> 00:11:19.721
Uh. it is!

319
00:11:19.804 --> 00:11:21.723
[ Giggles ]

320
00:11:21.806 --> 00:11:24.142
[ Laughing ]

321
00:11:24.225 --> 00:11:25.935
[ Giggling ]

322
00:11:25.977 --> 00:11:27.228
You let anyone do that?

323
00:11:27.312 --> 00:11:29.314
He gave us
all the money he had.

324
00:11:30.398 --> 00:11:33.193
[ Banging ]

325
00:11:30.398 --> 00:11:33.193
Morty: Hunh! Hunh! Hunh!

326
00:11:34.485 --> 00:11:36.279
Threat nullified.

327
00:11:36.321 --> 00:11:37.655
Hey. how 's your head?

328
00:11:37.697 --> 00:11:39.991
M-my vision's gettin'
pretty cloudy.

329
00:11:40.033 --> 00:11:43.828
B-but even I can see. heh.
y-you're almost free. Reese!

330
00:11:43.870 --> 00:11:45.663
[ Door creaks ]

331
00:11:45.705 --> 00:11:47.874
Yes! We're getting you
out of here!

332
00:11:50.501 --> 00:11:51.836
[ Engine starts ]

333
00:11:51.920 --> 00:11:55.173
[ Portal device whirring.
modem buzzing ]

334
00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:56.674
[ Ding! ]

335
00:11:56.716 --> 00:11:58.801
Ohh. that looks nice.

336
00:11:58.843 --> 00:12:01.179
Good.
Then that's your new home.

337
00:12:01.221 --> 00:12:03.348
[ Portal hums ]

338
00:12:05.808 --> 00:12:07.310
Wow.

339
00:12:05.808 --> 00:12:07.310
Huh.

340
00:12:07.352 --> 00:12:09.896
Expected a different
kind of catfish.

341
00:12:09.979 --> 00:12:11.231
Uh. 'scuse me.

342
00:12:11.314 --> 00:12:13.024
Is there still forest
around here?

343
00:12:13.107 --> 00:12:14.442
Whassat?
Oh. no.

344
00:12:14.525 --> 00:12:17.362
Not since the God
in the White Coat.

345
00:12:17.403 --> 00:12:20.615
He gave our world the gift
of metal and computer science.

346
00:12:20.657 --> 00:12:23.660
In return.
we run his holy silo.

347
00:12:23.701 --> 00:12:25.536
The younger hogs
resent our duty.

348
00:12:25.578 --> 00:12:28.164
Can't say I blame 'em.
If wages keep stagnatin'.

349
00:12:28.206 --> 00:12:30.041
maybe I'll do something worse!
Ha ha!

350
00:12:30.124 --> 00:12:33.044
Oh. wow. Yeah.
that-th-that guy's my grandpa.

351
00:12:33.086 --> 00:12:35.713
Th-this is Reese.
He. uh. he works for him. too.

352
00:12:35.755 --> 00:12:37.006
The password man.

353
00:12:37.048 --> 00:12:38.800
Oh. I may be
putting down roots here.

354
00:12:38.841 --> 00:12:40.593
Please do!
Now. if y'all excuse me.

355
00:12:40.677 --> 00:12:44.055
I'm needed at a high-tech
potato distillery.

356
00:12:44.097 --> 00:12:46.224
Well.
w-w-we did it. Reese.

357
00:12:46.307 --> 00:12:48.184
It's the first day
of the rest of your life.

358
00:12:48.226 --> 00:12:50.770
Before today. I was
a two-factor authenticator

359
00:12:50.853 --> 00:12:52.272
with a vague
Southern affect.

360
00:12:52.355 --> 00:12:54.649
Now I can be
whatever I want.

361
00:12:54.691 --> 00:12:58.069
Thank you. Morty.

362
00:12:54.691 --> 00:12:58.069
Uh. y-y-you're welcome.
Reese.

363
00:12:58.111 --> 00:13:01.030
Wade with the current.

364
00:12:58.111 --> 00:13:01.030
I'll probably
do somethin' else.

365
00:13:01.072 --> 00:13:03.741
Fishing's b-o-o-o-o-ring!

366
00:13:03.825 --> 00:13:05.576
[ Footsteps approaching ]

367
00:13:05.618 --> 00:13:07.078
Busy store.

368
00:13:07.120 --> 00:13:10.290
Plus. I had to run
with these <i>weird</i> legs.

369
00:13:12.625 --> 00:13:16.838
[ Humming. thunder crashes ]

370
00:13:19.257 --> 00:13:21.217
There we go.

371
00:13:21.259 --> 00:13:24.178
Bro. you made me dig
out the whole thing.

372
00:13:24.762 --> 00:13:26.472
Oh! Hey. hey. Rick.

373
00:13:26.556 --> 00:13:29.183
God damn it. Morty!
We just cracked the lock!

374
00:13:29.225 --> 00:13:30.852
Now I have to pay
this guy his full rate!

375
00:13:30.935 --> 00:13:33.271
I am <i>very</i> expensive.

376
00:13:33.354 --> 00:13:35.565
Where's Reese?

377
00:13:33.354 --> 00:13:35.565
Safe from you!

378
00:13:35.606 --> 00:13:37.442
I took him through
the landline portal

379
00:13:37.525 --> 00:13:40.278
and set him up with a new life
with his new hog friends.

380
00:13:40.361 --> 00:13:41.112
Oh. no.

381
00:13:41.154 --> 00:13:45.408
[ Machinery whirring ]

382
00:13:45.450 --> 00:13:49.162
<i>Rick Sanchez. we have
taken possession of
your password man.</i>

383
00:13:49.245 --> 00:13:51.122
<i>Long live
the Hog Resistance!</i>

384
00:13:51.205 --> 00:13:52.665
Morty. you dumb idiot.

385
00:13:52.749 --> 00:13:55.251
you think those vodka hogs
wouldn't fuck me over?

386
00:13:55.293 --> 00:13:57.462
Th-the good-natured
rustic thing is just an act!

387
00:13:57.503 --> 00:14:03.217
Their whole planet
runs on my tech. Morty!

388
00:14:03.301 --> 00:14:04.510
Whoaaaa!

389
00:14:04.594 --> 00:14:06.804
Wooooh!
Ooohahh! Ohh!

390
00:14:06.888 --> 00:14:08.222
I'm gonna fuckin' barf!

391
00:14:11.267 --> 00:14:14.729
<i>Rick Sanchez. you will
no longer subjugate
our homeworld!</i>

392
00:14:14.812 --> 00:14:15.938
<i>Fuck you!</i>

393
00:14:16.022 --> 00:14:18.191
-Go make my vodka!
<i>-No!</i>

394
00:14:18.232 --> 00:14:20.318
<i>We just got access
to your desktop...</i>

395
00:14:20.401 --> 00:14:22.904
<i>Deh? Ooh. are these
circles fucking?</i>

396
00:14:22.987 --> 00:14:24.489
They're making love!

397
00:14:24.572 --> 00:14:26.366
IT guy. rip that computer out!

398
00:14:27.825 --> 00:14:29.744
[ Gunfire ]

399
00:14:31.954 --> 00:14:33.748
[ Screaming in the distance ]

400
00:14:31.954 --> 00:14:33.748
Are Summer and Mom home?

401
00:14:33.831 --> 00:14:36.125
F-u-u-u-u-uck!

402
00:14:38.336 --> 00:14:39.837
Morty. grab on!

403
00:14:41.422 --> 00:14:43.800
-Wh-o-o-o-oa!
-Aaaah!

404
00:14:45.510 --> 00:14:47.428
[ Both grunting ]

405
00:14:48.721 --> 00:14:49.931
Aah!

406
00:14:51.099 --> 00:14:52.809
Why is the
furniture attacking us?

407
00:14:52.892 --> 00:14:54.310
Rick's been hacked!

408
00:14:54.394 --> 00:14:56.270
Because Morty assumed
that hogs in overalls

409
00:14:56.354 --> 00:14:57.980
couldn't also be hackers!

410
00:14:58.064 --> 00:14:59.107
Aah!

411
00:15:03.319 --> 00:15:05.530
Um. Dad. you're losing
a lot of blood.

412
00:15:05.613 --> 00:15:08.282
It's okay!
I can make more!

413
00:15:08.366 --> 00:15:09.534
Badass.

414
00:15:09.617 --> 00:15:12.620
{\an8}♪♪

415
00:15:12.703 --> 00:15:14.872
Stop replacing my stuff
with robots!

416
00:15:14.956 --> 00:15:16.457
You never noticed
the difference!

417
00:15:16.499 --> 00:15:18.543
<i>Rick lies to everyone!</i>

418
00:15:18.584 --> 00:15:21.129
<i>Doesn't that make
you wanna join the resistance?</i>

419
00:15:25.842 --> 00:15:27.468
Shit!
The floor is lava!

420
00:15:27.510 --> 00:15:29.470
Did you put that in
for defense or for fun?

421
00:15:29.512 --> 00:15:30.847
I don't remember!

422
00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:32.849
Ooh-hoo-ho-hoo!
Ho-ho-ho!

423
00:15:32.932 --> 00:15:34.267
You ever think about how
instead of wrapping yourself

424
00:15:34.308 --> 00:15:36.310
in infinite
layers of defense

425
00:15:36.352 --> 00:15:37.603
you could just
be nicer to people?

426
00:15:36.352 --> 00:15:37.603
[ Cellphone ringing ]

427
00:15:37.645 --> 00:15:38.896
Never once. Morty!

428
00:15:39.814 --> 00:15:43.818
Hog Hacker: <i>Rick Sanchez.
is your refrigerator running?</i>

429
00:15:43.901 --> 00:15:45.653
<i>Because you better
go and catch it!</i>

430
00:15:45.695 --> 00:15:47.447
You owe me.

431
00:15:47.488 --> 00:15:49.198
Wh-o-o-oa!

432
00:15:49.282 --> 00:15:50.658
[ Laughing ]

433
00:15:50.741 --> 00:15:52.493
Ooh-ugh-ah!

434
00:15:52.535 --> 00:15:53.619
Whoa-ho-ho-ho!

435
00:15:53.661 --> 00:15:55.413
Everyone. kill yourselves!

436
00:15:55.496 --> 00:15:57.457
I'll help!

437
00:15:55.496 --> 00:15:57.457
Huh?

438
00:15:57.498 --> 00:15:59.834
<i>[ Screaming. squelching ]</i>

439
00:15:59.917 --> 00:16:01.752
[ Jerry crying ]

440
00:16:01.836 --> 00:16:03.880
Listen to this.
It's the ocean or something.

441
00:16:03.963 --> 00:16:05.214
[ Whimpering ]

442
00:16:05.298 --> 00:16:07.800
Ohh-ugh. uhh!

443
00:16:09.135 --> 00:16:10.511
Thanks for
turning off the lava.

444
00:16:10.595 --> 00:16:11.971
[ All grunting ]

445
00:16:12.013 --> 00:16:13.389
You couldn't have
turned off everything?

446
00:16:13.473 --> 00:16:14.515
Ohh!

447
00:16:21.564 --> 00:16:22.648
[ Roars ]

448
00:16:22.690 --> 00:16:24.817
Emergency shutoff in my room.

449
00:16:25.401 --> 00:16:26.444
Run!

450
00:16:27.695 --> 00:16:29.197
Oh-ho-ho!
Ooh!

451
00:16:32.033 --> 00:16:33.534
Aaaah! Aaaaah! Unf!

452
00:16:33.576 --> 00:16:34.911
I hate living here!

453
00:16:34.994 --> 00:16:36.496
-Aaaaaaaaaah!
-Move!

454
00:16:38.039 --> 00:16:39.874
Hit that shut-off quick.
It stinks in here.

455
00:16:39.916 --> 00:16:41.667
Punching down.

456
00:16:41.709 --> 00:16:42.919
[ Zap! ]

457
00:16:43.002 --> 00:16:44.921
[ Electricity crackles ]

458
00:16:49.759 --> 00:16:52.303
-See? All fixed.
-Awesome.

459
00:16:53.554 --> 00:16:55.890
Th-thank goodness
you knocked out all that stuff.

460
00:16:55.973 --> 00:16:57.266
Yep.
Nothing electronic left

461
00:16:57.350 --> 00:16:59.352
that can be hacked
or turned against us.

462
00:16:59.393 --> 00:17:00.436
Salud!

463
00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:02.230
Ohh!
Aah!

464
00:17:07.026 --> 00:17:09.403
The Liberation of Hog Planet
is at hand.

465
00:17:09.445 --> 00:17:12.323
Prepare for your death.
Oppressor Sanchez.

466
00:17:12.406 --> 00:17:13.533
Reese. no!

467
00:17:14.784 --> 00:17:16.160
Run!

468
00:17:16.869 --> 00:17:18.246
Whoa.
New look for Reese.

469
00:17:18.329 --> 00:17:20.998
I don't like how many
adult friends Morty has.

470
00:17:24.252 --> 00:17:25.169
Gyaah!

471
00:17:25.253 --> 00:17:26.879
Rick.
use your implants!

472
00:17:26.921 --> 00:17:28.589
What part of
"nothing electronic"

473
00:17:28.631 --> 00:17:29.882
went over your head.
Morty?

474
00:17:29.924 --> 00:17:31.384
Hit him with pipes!

475
00:17:31.425 --> 00:17:33.970
[ Both grunting ]

476
00:17:34.053 --> 00:17:35.763
It's not doing anything!

477
00:17:35.846 --> 00:17:37.098
Whoa!

478
00:17:37.765 --> 00:17:39.141
-Aah!
-Aah!

479
00:17:41.477 --> 00:17:42.520
Oh!

480
00:17:42.853 --> 00:17:45.147
Sorry I'm d-doing this.
R-Rick.

481
00:17:45.231 --> 00:17:47.942
I think someone messed
with my h-h-head.

482
00:17:47.984 --> 00:17:49.569
Reese. it's me!
Remember?

483
00:17:49.610 --> 00:17:50.945
You told me it was normal

484
00:17:50.987 --> 00:17:52.613
to have one pube longer
than the others?

485
00:17:52.655 --> 00:17:54.824
Stop trying to override his
programming with love. Morty!

486
00:17:54.907 --> 00:17:56.617
Well. hitting him with pipes
isn't working!

487
00:17:56.659 --> 00:17:57.743
Ow!

488
00:17:58.536 --> 00:18:00.788
You can't love something
out of hurting you!

489
00:18:01.289 --> 00:18:02.623
Oh. you'd sure love
that to be true!

490
00:18:02.665 --> 00:18:03.791
Fuck you. Morty!

491
00:18:03.833 --> 00:18:05.209
-I hate you!
-I hate you!

492
00:18:05.293 --> 00:18:07.420
-I hate you! I hate you!
-I hate you! I hate you!

493
00:18:07.461 --> 00:18:09.547
I hate you! I hate you!
I hate you!

494
00:18:07.461 --> 00:18:09.547
I hate you! I hate you!

495
00:18:09.589 --> 00:18:12.258
I hate you!
I hate you! I hate you!

496
00:18:09.589 --> 00:18:12.258
I hate you!

497
00:18:12.300 --> 00:18:13.801
[ Electricity crackles ]

498
00:18:12.300 --> 00:18:13.801
Unh!

499
00:18:13.843 --> 00:18:15.344
Ahh.

500
00:18:15.428 --> 00:18:18.180
Y-y-you know what. Rick?
You two may f-f-fight.

501
00:18:18.264 --> 00:18:21.767
but you're the real d-d-deal.

502
00:18:21.809 --> 00:18:23.060
[ Machinery whirring down ]

503
00:18:25.646 --> 00:18:27.940
[ Armor clanking ]

504
00:18:29.442 --> 00:18:30.443
Huh.

505
00:18:30.484 --> 00:18:32.612
Probably
doesn't mean anything.

506
00:18:33.696 --> 00:18:34.989
Yep.

507
00:18:39.410 --> 00:18:41.412
[ Rumbling ]

508
00:18:41.954 --> 00:18:44.832
Hey. Grandpa. did you turn
the yard into a giant sinkhole

509
00:18:44.915 --> 00:18:46.125
when you dug out
the subbasement?

510
00:18:46.167 --> 00:18:47.710
It's fine.
It's just some tunnels.

511
00:18:47.793 --> 00:18:49.503
Are the tunnels
reinforced?

512
00:18:49.545 --> 00:18:51.881
Don't overthink the tunnels.
I have a handle on the tunnels.

513
00:18:51.964 --> 00:18:54.467
[ Vehicle beeping ]

514
00:18:58.387 --> 00:19:01.015
How much longer
is he gonna be Dad for?

515
00:19:01.057 --> 00:19:02.475
I like him.

516
00:19:01.057 --> 00:19:02.475
Me too.

517
00:19:02.516 --> 00:19:04.352
Summer just taught me
what "push-ups" are.

518
00:19:04.393 --> 00:19:06.896
I did.
He's fuckin' nailing them.

519
00:19:06.979 --> 00:19:09.190
-Mom?
-Oh. Uh. one more week?

520
00:19:09.231 --> 00:19:12.068
-What?
-No. no. you're right.

521
00:19:12.151 --> 00:19:15.488
It was good getting to know you.
"The Smiths."

522
00:19:15.529 --> 00:19:17.948
Wait!

523
00:19:15.529 --> 00:19:17.948
Morty. him leaving
was your idea.

524
00:19:18.032 --> 00:19:20.493
Well.
I have another idea.

525
00:19:25.665 --> 00:19:26.582
[ Breathes ]

526
00:19:26.666 --> 00:19:29.377
[ Both scream ]

527
00:19:29.418 --> 00:19:32.004
Ugh!!
Why do I taste rainbow wax?

528
00:19:32.046 --> 00:19:34.215
Why do you know what
that tastes like?

529
00:19:35.216 --> 00:19:36.550
[ Bones crack ]
Oh. Ah!

530
00:19:36.634 --> 00:19:37.677
[ Grunting ]

531
00:19:37.718 --> 00:19:39.220
How 's it feel?

532
00:19:39.261 --> 00:19:42.056
Not as wet as the last guy.
but I'll fix that.

533
00:19:42.098 --> 00:19:45.976
[ Grunting. lips smacking ]

534
00:19:46.060 --> 00:19:47.978
I'm glad you're getting
to live on. Reese.

535
00:19:48.020 --> 00:19:50.272
And getting a pretty sweet rig
out of the deal.

536
00:19:50.731 --> 00:19:52.942
I hope you have
a good life out there.

537
00:19:53.025 --> 00:19:54.694
I...
I love you.

538
00:19:54.735 --> 00:19:57.738
And I love how much matter
you're made of.

539
00:19:57.822 --> 00:20:00.408
I'm leaving now. to do things
that are my business.

540
00:20:00.449 --> 00:20:02.910
There is a place called Skyzone.

541
00:20:02.952 --> 00:20:04.745
Do not visit me there.

542
00:20:05.913 --> 00:20:07.248
[ Sighs ]

543
00:20:07.331 --> 00:20:08.999
What. you gonna keep
sighing until I notice?

544
00:20:09.083 --> 00:20:10.835
I'm just breathing.

545
00:20:09.083 --> 00:20:10.835
He's alive. Morty.

546
00:20:10.918 --> 00:20:12.503
You're welcome.

547
00:20:13.879 --> 00:20:15.881
Gaaaah!
Fuckin' hogs.

548
00:20:15.923 --> 00:20:17.091
Fuckin' Morty.

549
00:20:17.133 --> 00:20:18.092
Cost me a flask.

550
00:20:18.134 --> 00:20:19.427
[ Beep! ]

551
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:21.137
[ Explosions.
Hog-people screaming ]

552
00:20:21.220 --> 00:20:23.806
[burps] Learned my lesson.
No more portal flasks.

553
00:20:23.889 --> 00:20:25.433
Mmm. mmm!

554
00:20:25.516 --> 00:20:27.685
Ahh.

555
00:20:27.768 --> 00:20:30.646
Mmm. mmm.
Mmm.

556
00:20:30.730 --> 00:20:31.772
Ahh.

557
00:20:31.814 --> 00:20:34.692
Mmm. mmm. mmm.

558
00:20:34.775 --> 00:20:37.945
[burps] Morty. I-I
can tell you're disgusted...

559
00:20:37.987 --> 00:20:39.196
[ Burps ]

560
00:20:39.238 --> 00:20:41.282
...but you're gonna be
just like me!

561
00:20:41.323 --> 00:20:44.118
It's a disease. Morty!
A genetic disease!

562
00:20:44.201 --> 00:20:45.870
It's already in you.
Morty!

563
00:20:45.953 --> 00:20:55.880
{\an8}♪♪

564
00:20:55.963 --> 00:21:05.890
{\an8}♪♪

565
00:21:05.973 --> 00:21:15.900
{\an8}♪♪

566
00:21:15.983 --> 00:21:16.984
[ Groaning ]

567
00:21:17.026 --> 00:21:19.111
H-hey. buddy. y-you good?

568
00:21:19.153 --> 00:21:22.573
F-u-u-uck you. Morty.
you little piece of shit.

569
00:21:22.615 --> 00:21:24.158
You think you're better
than me. Morty?!

570
00:21:24.200 --> 00:21:25.451
I'm gonna --
I'm gonna kill you!

571
00:21:25.493 --> 00:21:26.827
I-I'll kill you!!

572
00:21:25.493 --> 00:21:26.827
[ Knock on door ]

573
00:21:26.911 --> 00:21:28.245
Hey. guys! I'm Rex.

574
00:21:28.329 --> 00:21:29.789
I just moved in next door.

575
00:21:29.830 --> 00:21:31.874
and I love "Minecraft"
and skateboarding!

576
00:21:31.957 --> 00:21:33.000
-Unh!
-Aah!

577
00:21:33.083 --> 00:21:34.585
[ Groaning ]

578
00:21:34.668 --> 00:21:36.003
Aaah! Aah!

579
00:21:36.045 --> 00:21:39.673
Wait- wait. he's- he's not--

580
00:21:36.045 --> 00:21:39.673
[ Cellphone ringing ]

581
00:21:39.757 --> 00:21:41.258
Georgie Boy!

582
00:21:41.300 --> 00:21:44.428
M-Morty. w-would-- would
you believe my unrelated friend.

583
00:21:44.512 --> 00:21:46.931
Georgie Boy.
wants to hang?

584
00:21:47.014 --> 00:21:48.307
Howdy. fellas!

585
00:21:48.349 --> 00:21:50.351
Georgie Boy!
Georgie Boy!

586
00:21:48.349 --> 00:21:50.351
But -- Oh...

587
00:21:50.392 --> 00:21:52.561
Georgie Boy!
Georgie Boy!

588
00:21:53.938 --> 00:21:55.564
Did you get any of that?
